steps for work with git
=======================

1.- install git in your pc
2.- configure git in your pc (write name and email)
3.- add origin from repo url for connect my proyect with my repo
4.- download all changes from repository
5.- create branches in my project
6.- download changes for each one branches
7.- send changes from my pc to my repo (for each one branches)


comands
=======
( we need go to my project from terminal or comand line)

git init 			-> init git inside my project 
git brach --all 		-> show me all branches (local - remotes)
git remote add origin <url>	-> add the repo url in my project
git add 			-> add all changes to stage work
	example : git add -A  -> add all changes
		  git add filename.extension  -> add the specified files
		  
git log 			-> show me the commits history

git checkout <branchname > 		-> switch branch 		  

git checkout -b <branchname >  		-> create branch and move to this		 
		  
		 		  
git branch <branchname>

git branch -d <branchname>


git pull 				-> update our project in pc with the last changes in my repo

git push 				-> update the repo with the changes in my pc




















		  
		  
		  



